x4freetext: Cross sections for the Al(n,xn) and Al(n,x-gamma)
reactions between 1 and 20 MeV
Oak Ridge Electron Linear Accelerator
1132-grams of aluminum, better than 99% pure, shaped
in annular ring, 25-cm outer diameter, 15-cm inner
diameter, 1.3-cm thick.
Time of flight used to determine incident neutron
energy and flux. Sample and shadow bar were removed
for this measurement. Sample placed 37.7-meters from
neutron source. Pulse shape discrimination used to
separate neutron and gamma events. Background
measurements made with sample removed.
NE-213 scintillator with shadow bar placed on
samples ring axis.
Plastic scintillator placed on edge of incident neutron
beam 30-meters from source for normalization of data.
Data corrected only for gamma-ray self-absorption.
Statistical errors, which include contributions
due to background.
Uncertainty due to overall normalization about 10%.
Approved by G.L.Morgan, 1982/3/12.
Reference corrected.
Reactions corrected. Converted to new date
formats, lower case.
